WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.734
(talking drowned out by peaceful music)

2
00:00:48.151 --> 00:00:51.410
(footsteps clicking)

3
00:00:51.410 --> 00:00:52.243
- Lucien?

4
00:00:57.921 --> 00:00:59.338
Well, how was it?

5
00:01:00.257 --> 00:01:01.257
- All right.

6
00:01:02.227 --> 00:01:04.477
- Didn't the teacher say anything to you?

7
00:01:06.199 --> 00:01:07.032
- No.

8
00:01:08.280 --> 00:01:09.530
- And the other children?

9
00:01:12.102 --> 00:01:12.935
- Nothing.

10
00:01:17.570 --> 00:01:19.520
- I've been worrying about you all day.

11
00:01:20.696 --> 00:01:22.246
Perhaps it'll be all right now.

12
00:01:34.191 --> 00:01:37.191
(suspenseful music)

13
00:01:42.784 --> 00:01:44.670
(door clatters)

14
00:01:44.670 --> 00:01:46.853
Come on Marie, the food's out already.

15
00:01:54.620 --> 00:01:55.890
- Little coward.

16
00:01:55.890 --> 00:01:57.343
- That's enough Marie.

17
00:01:58.667 --> 00:02:01.097
- Oh ma, why did you let him do it?

18
00:02:01.097 --> 00:02:03.610
You should have made him go to school.

19
00:02:03.610 --> 00:02:06.690
- He did go to school,
leave the poor boy alone.

20
00:02:06.690 --> 00:02:08.550
- He did not go to school.

21
00:02:08.550 --> 00:02:10.400
I don't know where he's been all day,

22
00:02:10.400 --> 00:02:12.173
but it certainly wasn't at school.

23
00:02:13.770 --> 00:02:14.603
- Lucien?

24
00:02:16.140 --> 00:02:18.230
- I met the school teacher on the way home

25
00:02:18.230 --> 00:02:21.010
and he asked me where Lucien was today,

26
00:02:21.010 --> 00:02:22.853
and was everything all right.

27
00:02:23.790 --> 00:02:24.623
- Lucien.

28
00:02:26.287 --> 00:02:29.204
(melancholy music)

29
00:02:39.713 --> 00:02:42.597
- Teacher When I'm
finished with this drawing

30
00:02:42.597 --> 00:02:45.230
I'd like the older ones to copy it down

31
00:02:45.230 --> 00:02:46.743
in their exercise books,

32
00:02:47.700 --> 00:02:51.033
we'll have more time after
the break if you need it.

33
00:02:52.876 --> 00:02:54.648
- Do you know what Lucien Morell has done?

34
00:02:54.648 --> 00:02:56.579
He dropped Dani's kitten into the ravine

35
00:02:56.579 --> 00:02:57.916
and Dani tried to get it back.

36
00:02:57.916 --> 00:03:02.536
He pushed him and Dani
fell in and broke his leg.

37
00:03:02.536 --> 00:03:05.203
Do you know what Lucien Morell did?

38
00:03:05.203 --> 00:03:08.286
He pushed my brother over the ravine.

39
00:03:09.270 --> 00:03:12.170
- Teacher And this will be
for the younger ones as well.

40
00:03:15.330 --> 00:03:16.330
I'm going to begin

41
00:03:16.330 --> 00:03:20.523
with some of the ways in
which it spreads diseases.

42
00:03:23.230 --> 00:03:25.493
It's such an innocent
looking little thing.

43
00:03:27.810 --> 00:03:30.363
And yet it can cause so much harm.

44
00:03:32.696 --> 00:03:33.793
(book slams)

45
00:03:33.793 --> 00:03:36.793
(children laughing)

46
00:03:45.700 --> 00:03:46.570
- Teacher Bernard.

47
00:03:46.570 --> 00:03:47.830
- Sir?

48
00:03:47.830 --> 00:03:49.380
- Bring me that piece of paper.

49
00:03:57.540 --> 00:03:58.440
Put it on my desk.

50
00:04:04.006 --> 00:04:07.006
(children laughing)

51
00:04:14.930 --> 00:04:16.800
Is this your writing Annette?

52
00:04:16.800 --> 00:04:17.717
- Yes sir.

53
00:04:18.760 --> 00:04:21.230
- Do you really think this is necessary?

54
00:04:21.230 --> 00:04:22.100
- It's true sir.

55
00:04:22.100 --> 00:04:23.592
- I know it's true.

56
00:04:23.592 --> 00:04:26.603
I said do you really think it's necessary?

57
00:04:27.960 --> 00:04:31.350
I find it difficult to
understand Lucien's behavior,

58
00:04:31.350 --> 00:04:32.220
and we're all very glad

59
00:04:32.220 --> 00:04:34.270
it didn't turn out any worse than it did.

60
00:04:35.490 --> 00:04:36.510
No doubt he'll think twice

61
00:04:36.510 --> 00:04:38.743
before doing any such stupid thing again.

62
00:04:40.030 --> 00:04:44.460
But if I hear any more malicious
gossip over this matter

63
00:04:44.460 --> 00:04:47.130
I shall be very, very cross.

64
00:04:54.436 --> 00:04:57.603
(children chattering)

65
00:05:07.494 --> 00:05:10.411
(melancholy music)

66
00:05:13.663 --> 00:05:15.830
(sobbing)

67
00:05:46.527 --> 00:05:49.194
(tools tapping)

68
00:06:00.937 --> 00:06:02.437
- Yes that's good.

69
00:06:06.076 --> 00:06:07.326
Yes, I like it.

70
00:06:12.957 --> 00:06:16.713
Oh yeah, you can't have a
Noah's Ark without lions.

71
00:06:22.394 --> 00:06:25.061
(tools tapping)

72
00:06:34.030 --> 00:06:37.753
You know you'll soon be able
to sell some of your models?

73
00:06:37.753 --> 00:06:39.420
Would you like that?

74
00:06:40.488 --> 00:06:42.125
- Do you really mean that?

75
00:06:42.125 --> 00:06:43.143
- Course I do.

76
00:06:43.143 --> 00:06:47.260
There's a man in the village
who sells my carvings,

77
00:06:47.260 --> 00:06:50.639
we could take some of
yours and show them to him.

78
00:06:50.639 --> 00:06:52.805
(peaceful music)

79
00:06:52.805 --> 00:06:55.472
(tools tapping)

80
00:08:11.210 --> 00:08:14.093
- At school today they announced
a handwork competition.

81
00:08:15.270 --> 00:08:16.610
- Oh yes?

82
00:08:16.610 --> 00:08:18.060
What's the prize going to be?

83
00:08:19.166 --> 00:08:22.843
- I don't know but that
doesn't really matter.

84
00:08:24.100 --> 00:08:26.270
- Aren't you going to enter?

85
00:08:26.270 --> 00:08:31.270
- Yes, I'll show them I'm
better than all of them.

86
00:08:31.747 --> 00:08:33.233
- Oh I'm sure you are.

87
00:08:35.120 --> 00:08:36.683
Was there ever any doubt?

88
00:08:42.140 --> 00:08:44.223
- I'm going to carve a galloping horse.

89
00:08:47.240 --> 00:08:50.953
Its mane and its tail,
streaming out behind it.

90
00:08:53.020 --> 00:08:54.593
- But why try a horse?

91
00:08:55.550 --> 00:08:58.253
Why not use your Noah's Ark?

92
00:08:59.290 --> 00:09:01.643
- It's a present, for a little boy.

93
00:09:03.740 --> 00:09:04.573
- Your brother?

94
00:09:07.300 --> 00:09:10.060
- No, he lives near me.

95
00:09:10.060 --> 00:09:12.550
He got hurt in an accident.

96
00:09:12.550 --> 00:09:14.243
- Oh, badly?

97
00:09:16.600 --> 00:09:17.633
- Broke his leg.

98
00:09:19.220 --> 00:09:20.053
- Oh dear.

99
00:09:23.550 --> 00:09:25.493
Aren't you going to tell me about it?

100
00:09:30.667 --> 00:09:33.667
(suspenseful music)

101
00:09:38.380 --> 00:09:40.570
- He was playing up in the mountains

102
00:09:42.450 --> 00:09:44.353
and a boy came and teased him.

103
00:09:45.453 --> 00:09:48.640
Said he would drop his
kitten over a ravine

104
00:09:50.830 --> 00:09:55.830
he wasn't really going
to, and then it happened.

105
00:09:56.380 --> 00:09:58.430
And Dani went after it, I couldn't stop--

106
00:10:14.372 --> 00:10:16.122
- What are you doing?

107
00:10:18.199 --> 00:10:19.490
- You don't want me here now.

108
00:10:19.490 --> 00:10:20.890
- Woodcarver Why ever not?

109
00:10:22.130 --> 00:10:23.203
- No-one else does.

110
00:10:26.510 --> 00:10:29.113
- What am I going to do
for a friend if you go now?

111
00:10:30.480 --> 00:10:31.863
Come, sit down.

112
00:10:34.270 --> 00:10:35.103
Come on.

113
00:10:38.320 --> 00:10:39.183
That's better.

114
00:10:42.520 --> 00:10:43.507
How is he now?

115
00:10:46.380 --> 00:10:49.220
- His sister won't let me go and see him.

116
00:10:49.220 --> 00:10:52.923
- Woodcarver Oh, is
she still angry with you?

117
00:10:54.010 --> 00:10:56.423
- She's always telling
other people about it.

118
00:10:57.391 --> 00:11:00.633
- Hmm, it won't be easy.

119
00:11:03.810 --> 00:11:05.663
People are slow to forget.

120
00:11:08.400 --> 00:11:12.090
It's a good thing you're
doing, stick at it.

121
00:11:12.090 --> 00:11:15.162
Go on, don't let her discourage you.

122
00:11:15.162 --> 00:11:17.912
(horse whinnies)

123
00:11:42.975 --> 00:11:43.998
- Monsieur Burnier There's
Annette on the bridge.

124
00:11:43.998 --> 00:11:46.081
- Dani There's Annette.

125
00:11:48.426 --> 00:11:49.536
- Monsieur Burnier Hello Annette.

126
00:11:49.536 --> 00:11:50.605
- Hello.
- Hello.

127
00:11:50.605 --> 00:11:52.390
- I didn't think you
were going to get back.

128
00:11:52.390 --> 00:11:53.540
- Grandma Burnier Hello.

129
00:11:53.540 --> 00:11:55.540
- Now we can all go for a walk together.

130
00:11:58.570 --> 00:12:01.286
- I'm afraid it's a bit soon for that.

131
00:12:01.286 --> 00:12:02.420
- Why?

132
00:12:02.420 --> 00:12:03.841
- Come on Dani.

133
00:12:03.841 --> 00:12:04.674
- Oh.

134
00:12:05.720 --> 00:12:06.553
- Careful.

135
00:12:13.174 --> 00:12:14.341
There you are.

136
00:12:18.171 --> 00:12:19.088
- Mind out.

137
00:12:22.027 --> 00:12:22.860
Watch me.

138
00:12:25.121 --> 00:12:27.849
- That's splendid Dani.

139
00:12:27.849 --> 00:12:29.020
That's splendid.

140
00:12:29.020 --> 00:12:32.224
- Look, one of my legs is
shorter than the other.

141
00:12:32.224 --> 00:12:33.950
- Oh Dani don't be silly.

142
00:12:33.950 --> 00:12:36.867
(melancholy music)

143
00:12:39.213 --> 00:12:40.046
What is it?

144
00:12:41.370 --> 00:12:42.980
What's the matter?

145
00:12:42.980 --> 00:12:46.303
- Go on Dani, show your Granny
how you can climb the steps.

146
00:13:00.739 --> 00:13:01.572
- Annette.

147
00:13:04.225 --> 00:13:06.630
Dani won't ever walk again properly.

148
00:13:06.630 --> 00:13:07.880
He'll always have a limp.

149
00:13:09.389 --> 00:13:12.306
(melancholy music)

150
00:13:27.360 --> 00:13:28.193
Eh up.

151
00:13:40.044 --> 00:13:40.877
Come on.

152
00:13:59.705 --> 00:14:02.622
(melancholy music)

153
00:14:38.660 --> 00:14:40.327
- It's a Noah's Ark.

154
00:14:41.567 --> 00:14:43.113
I made it for Dani.

155
00:14:47.977 --> 00:14:50.052
- Do you know what you've done?

156
00:14:50.052 --> 00:14:52.739
(suspenseful music)

157
00:14:52.739 --> 00:14:55.975
(wood smashes)

158
00:14:55.975 --> 00:14:58.558
Don't you ever come here again.

159
00:14:59.612 --> 00:15:02.612
(melancholy music)

160
00:15:12.528 --> 00:15:14.881
- Madame Morell What's the matter?

161
00:15:14.881 --> 00:15:16.381
Can't you tell me?

162
00:15:18.428 --> 00:15:19.261
Hmm?

163
00:15:22.573 --> 00:15:25.240
(saw scraping)

164
00:15:28.330 --> 00:15:29.163
- I'm sorry.

165
00:15:30.657 --> 00:15:32.824
That can't have been easy.

166
00:15:35.026 --> 00:15:39.577
I hope this doesn't make
you want to give up carving.

167
00:15:42.403 --> 00:15:43.867
- It's all right for you.

168
00:15:47.292 --> 00:15:49.542
- Maybe, we'll have to see.

169
00:15:51.507 --> 00:15:54.090
(saw scraping)

170
00:16:04.120 --> 00:16:06.510
- Oh, I've got something for you.

171
00:16:06.510 --> 00:16:07.353
Hi, here it is

172
00:16:07.353 --> 00:16:08.350
- Oh, thank you.

173
00:16:08.350 --> 00:16:09.813
- Hey, have you heard?

174
00:16:09.813 --> 00:16:12.080
- The young Burnier child's
going to have a permanent limp.

175
00:16:12.080 --> 00:16:12.913
- No.

176
00:16:13.991 --> 00:16:15.003
- Aye.

177
00:16:15.003 --> 00:16:16.120
- What a shame.

178
00:16:16.120 --> 00:16:17.793
- It's not right is it?

179
00:16:20.430 --> 00:16:22.360
He should be locked up, he should.

180
00:16:22.360 --> 00:16:23.910
- All right just give him time.

181
00:16:25.110 --> 00:16:28.109
- Girl Oh Annette, is
this for the competition?

182
00:16:28.109 --> 00:16:29.713
- Girl Gosh it's marvelous isn't it?

183
00:16:29.713 --> 00:16:32.170
- Annette I was making
it for Dani anyway.

184
00:16:32.170 --> 00:16:34.797
- Oh Annette it's bound to win the prize.

185
00:16:34.797 --> 00:16:37.510
- No, I think Bernard's
going to get the prize.

186
00:16:37.510 --> 00:16:39.863
- Oh we've got a dog just like that.

187
00:16:39.863 --> 00:16:43.053
- It's not a dog you idiot, it's a bear.

188
00:16:43.053 --> 00:16:45.550
- Girl Oh I'm sorry, I
really did think it was a dog.

189
00:16:45.550 --> 00:16:48.050
- Come on, anyone can see it's a bear.

190
00:16:51.369 --> 00:16:54.286
(melancholy music)

191
00:16:58.210 --> 00:17:00.960
(tools scraping)

192
00:18:42.233 --> 00:18:45.816
- You're not as stupid
as you look are you?

193
00:18:48.580 --> 00:18:50.910
- You'll see, when you win the prize

194
00:18:50.910 --> 00:18:52.810
they'll all want to be your friends.

195
00:18:57.884 --> 00:18:59.467
Come on, let's eat.

196
00:19:10.139 --> 00:19:13.139
(suspenseful music)

197
00:19:59.891 --> 00:20:02.558
(wood cracking)

198
00:20:20.512 --> 00:20:21.345
- Annette!

199
00:20:23.931 --> 00:20:28.614
Look what I found in the woodpile.

200
00:20:28.614 --> 00:20:32.970
I found a rhinoceros, a
buffalo and a tortoise.

201
00:20:32.970 --> 00:20:36.361
I think the fairies made them, don't you?

202
00:20:36.361 --> 00:20:37.411
- Don't be so stupid.

203
00:20:43.848 --> 00:20:46.765
(melancholy music)

204
00:21:21.150 --> 00:21:22.670
- Mama have you taken my horse?

205
00:21:22.670 --> 00:21:26.600
- Madam Morell No, Marie
have you taken Lucien's horse?

206
00:21:26.600 --> 00:21:27.433
- Marie No.

207
00:21:28.330 --> 00:21:29.163
- Madam Morell Are you sure

208
00:21:29.163 --> 00:21:31.150
you didn't bring it in with you?

209
00:21:31.150 --> 00:21:32.680
- No.

210
00:21:32.680 --> 00:21:34.663
- Marie Could it have
blown off the balcony?

211
00:21:38.440 --> 00:21:39.273
- Oh no.

212
00:21:43.610 --> 00:21:46.610
(melancholy music)

213
00:21:57.243 --> 00:21:58.892
- Oh Lucien.

214
00:21:58.892 --> 00:21:59.926
- Has it broken?

215
00:21:59.926 --> 00:22:01.075
- Madam Morell How could it!

216
00:22:01.075 --> 00:22:02.596
- Oh, somebody's trodden on it.

217
00:22:02.596 --> 00:22:05.847
- Why can't people mind
where they're going?

218
00:22:05.847 --> 00:22:06.680
Oh.

219
00:22:07.571 --> 00:22:09.960
(melancholy music)

220
00:22:09.960 --> 00:22:13.093
Isn't there anything we can do with it?

221
00:22:24.541 --> 00:22:27.458
(melancholy music)

222
00:23:31.330 --> 00:23:32.824
- Oh hello.

223
00:23:32.824 --> 00:23:33.657
- Hi.

224
00:23:36.330 --> 00:23:38.130
- Woodcarver How goes the carving?

225
00:23:39.140 --> 00:23:41.785
When are you going to win that prize?

226
00:23:41.785 --> 00:23:43.485
- I'm not going to win that prize.

227
00:23:44.510 --> 00:23:45.803
My horse is all smashed.

228
00:23:47.033 --> 00:23:47.866
- Oh no.

229
00:23:50.010 --> 00:23:51.193
Oh I am sorry.

230
00:23:56.261 --> 00:24:01.261
- It fell over and someone
must have trampled on it.

231
00:24:01.380 --> 00:24:03.943
Now I can't enter anything
for the competition.

232
00:24:05.525 --> 00:24:10.525
- Well, you could enter something else.

233
00:24:10.956 --> 00:24:12.910
What about the chamois set you did?

234
00:24:12.910 --> 00:24:14.013
That was quite good.

235
00:24:15.270 --> 00:24:17.120
- I didn't have the proper tools then

236
00:24:18.560 --> 00:24:20.643
and they'll think I
can't do anything better.

237
00:24:21.780 --> 00:24:24.380
- Woodcarver Well, does
it matter what they think?

238
00:24:25.580 --> 00:24:26.760
- Yes.

239
00:24:26.760 --> 00:24:27.593
- Why?

240
00:24:29.700 --> 00:24:33.193
- Because they all hate me
and they think I'm no good.

241
00:24:35.006 --> 00:24:36.930
- And you think that winning that prize

242
00:24:36.930 --> 00:24:38.680
will make them think better of you?

243
00:24:40.774 --> 00:24:41.691
They won't.

244
00:24:45.270 --> 00:24:47.523
- Then what's the point of trying?

245
00:24:48.540 --> 00:24:51.840
- Because you have to earn
the love and respect of others

246
00:24:53.350 --> 00:24:56.303
and you'll never do that by
doing things for yourself.

247
00:24:59.550 --> 00:25:01.700
But who am I to be talking of winning

248
00:25:01.700 --> 00:25:03.963
the love and respect of other people?

249
00:25:04.930 --> 00:25:05.763
- Yes.

250
00:25:10.420 --> 00:25:11.253
- Come here.

251
00:25:19.397 --> 00:25:22.150
I hope you can keep a secret,

252
00:25:22.150 --> 00:25:24.150
because I'm going to tell you something

253
00:25:24.150 --> 00:25:26.053
I've never told anyone else.

254
00:25:33.140 --> 00:25:34.623
I robbed a bank once.

255
00:25:38.170 --> 00:25:41.143
Oh it's all right this isn't it, sit down.

256
00:25:46.120 --> 00:25:48.910
I used to work at the bank once.

257
00:25:48.910 --> 00:25:53.800
I stole the money bit by bit
over a long period of time

258
00:25:53.800 --> 00:25:54.963
until they caught me.

259
00:25:55.910 --> 00:25:57.143
They put me in prison.

260
00:26:02.000 --> 00:26:03.853
I left my wife, Anna,

261
00:26:04.740 --> 00:26:06.723
to look after two small children.

262
00:26:09.440 --> 00:26:10.273
She.

263
00:26:12.353 --> 00:26:13.186
No.

264
00:26:19.482 --> 00:26:21.643
She was a good woman.

265
00:26:24.335 --> 00:26:25.313
A godly woman.

266
00:26:29.868 --> 00:26:30.701
And it...

267
00:26:32.830 --> 00:26:33.747
It killed her.

268
00:26:36.232 --> 00:26:38.232
The humiliation that is.

269
00:26:39.720 --> 00:26:44.513
She just couldn't take it.

270
00:26:51.389 --> 00:26:56.389
My two boys didn't know me
when I got out of prison.

